originalText.text: Delicious, is what this place is. Got the Caesar salad with chicken and it was finger licking delicious. Chicken was perfectly spiced and the dressing was just right. Will come back and also try tacos here too.

originalText.text:
I'm a big fan of this little gem within the Urban Space. It's got a truly authentic feel, similar to La Esquina nearby.

There are three directions you can go:
(a) Tacos - get three tacos, sample everything they have, and it will cost you $13.23. You won't get the rice and beans or the chips, but you can load up on pickled red onion and hot sauces. That little orange Salsa Picante is spicy, FYI. Everything is cooked perfectly and topped with guac and cotija cheese. Can't go wrong.

(b) Bowl - lots of people opted for this. You only get one protein, but you get the rice, beans, guac, sour cream and apparently CHIPS in the bowl. This is a great option

(c) Quesadilla/burrito - haven't tried these yet but this is the next frontier!

All in all, it's higher quality food than Chipotle, and you also don't feel like you're on some kind of assembly line. The staff works super quickly and diligently, and you're greeted with a smile. A+ place for quick but good Mexican good.
